1. What is HTML?
Ans- HTML is HyperText Markup Language.Used to create and structure website


2. What is the difference between HTML and HTML5?
Ans- HTML5 is the new version of HTML 
     HTML is the general markup language it's been for many years now.


3. What are semantic tags in HTML?
Ans- header,footer,section,nav


4. What is the difference between <div> and <span>?
Ans- div is block level element and span is inline level 


5. What is the difference between id and class?
Ans- id is unique and class is reuseable.


6. What are block-level and inline elements?
Ans- block-level elements are (div,p) and inline element are (span,a)
7. What is the purpose of the alt attribute?


8. What are meta tags?
Ans- metadata like charset and viewport.


9. What is CSS?
Ans- CSS is standard stylesheet language and CSS types are inline, internal, external.


10. What are the different ways to apply CSS?
Ans-Inline CSS, Internal CSS, External CSS.


11. Explain the CSS Box Model.
Ans-The CSS box model is essentially a box that wraps and there components are content, padding, margin, border


12. What is the difference between Margin and Padding?
Ans- Margin outside and padding inside


13. What is CSS Specificity?
Ans- inline, id, class, element


14. What is the difference between display: none and visibility: hidden?
Ans- none display hide element and visibility: hidden hides but content space remains.


15. What is the difference between Relative, Absolute, Fixed, and Sticky positioning?
Ans- Position: relative; is positioned relative to its normal position in the document flow.
     Absolute:Element is positioned relative to the nearest positioned ancestor
     Fixed:Element is positioned relative to the viewport
     Sticky: Toggles between a relative and fixed position, depending on the scroll position.


16. What is Flexbox?
Ans- Justify-content: Horizontally 
     align-item: Vertically


17. What is CSS Grid?
Ans- CSS grid is a layout that divides webpage into rows and columns.


18. What is the difference between Flexbox and Grid?
Ans- Flexbox is a one-dimensional layout model and Grid is two-dimensional layout model.


19. What is Responsive Web Design?
Ans- Responsive web design is to view in multiple devices, like desktop view, mobile view, tablet view, ipad mini view,etc.


20. What are Media Queries?
Ans- Media queries is use to create desktop view into mobile,tablet,ipad,etc Responsive CSS example @media (max-width 500px)
